---
import MelvinLayout from '../../../layouts/MelvinLayout.astro';
---

<MelvinLayout 
    title="Service as Education"
    description="Melvin Lim's community service journey. Insights from Guide Dogs Singapore, Youth Corps, and Senior Care volunteering."
>
    <section class="page-header container">
        <span class="eyebrow">The Heart</span>
        <h1>Service as Education</h1>
        <p class="lead">Leadership that is detached from the ground is fragile. Service keeps me rooted in reality.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="container">
        
        <article class="service-case">
            <div class="service-meta">
                <span class="org-name">Youth Corps Singapore</span>
                <span class="role-name">Migrant Badminton Pgm • 2023</span>
                <div class="image-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/images/projects/melvin/youth-corps.png" alt="Youth Corps Singapore" class="service-img" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="service-body">
                <h2>Bridging the Dormitory Gap.</h2>
                <p>
                    At Terusan RC, I played badminton with migrant workers who labor 15 hours a day to build our city. The stereotype of them being "cold" shatteredinstantly—they were spontaneous, kind, and eagerness to teach us carrom.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>The Realization:</strong> 16 men in one room. It was a stark contrast to my own life. True inclusivity means building bridges, not just acknowledging them from a distance.
                </p>
            </div>
        </article>

        <hr class="divider">

        <article class="service-case">
            <div class="service-meta">
                <span class="org-name">Guide Dogs Singapore</span>
                <span class="role-name">Flag Day • 2024</span>
                <div class="image-wrapper">
                    <img src="/assets/images/projects/melvin/guide-dogs.jpg" alt="Guide Dogs Singapore Flag Day" class="service-img" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="service-body">
                <h2>Accessibility is Dignity.</h2>
                <p>
                    Stepping onto the streets for Flag Day forced me past the fear of rejection. Advocating for the visually impaired isn't just about funds; it's about signaling to the community that <em>everyone</em> deserves to navigate our city with dignity.
                </p>
            </div>
        </article>
        
        <hr class="divider">

        <article class="service-case">
            <div class="service-meta">
                <span class="org-name">Ahmad Ibrahim Secondary</span>
                <span class="role-name">Origin Project • 2020</span>
            </div>
            <div class="service-body">
                <h2>Roots: The Friendly Canteen.</h2>
                <p>
                    Long before GDS, I led the <strong>Visually Impaired Friendly Canteen Project</strong> in secondary school. It was my first lesson in universal design: how physical spaces either include or exclude the marginalized.
                </p>
                <p><strong>The Legacy:</strong> This 4-year journey through Scouts and Student Council formed the foundation of the leader I am today.</p>
            </div>
        </article>

    </div>

</MelvinLayout>

<style>
    .page-header {
        padding-top: 8rem;
        padding-bottom: 4rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    }

    .eyebrow {
        font-family: var(--mv-font-sans);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        color: var(--mv-accent);
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 3.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .lead {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        max-width: 600px;
    }

    .service-case {
        padding: 6rem 0;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
        gap: 4rem;
    }

    .service-meta {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--mv-accent);
        padding-top: 1rem;
    }

    .org-name {
        display: block;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--mv-text-main);
    }

    .role-name {
        font-family: var(--mv-font-mono);
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .service-body h2 {
        font-size: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--mv-text-main);
    }

    .service-body p {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--mv-text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 700px;
    }

    .service-body strong {
        color: var(--mv-text-main);
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .divider {
        border: 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
        margin: 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .service-case {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            gap: 2rem;
            padding: 4rem 0;
        }
        
        .service-meta {
            border-top: none;
            border-left: 1px solid var(--mv-accent);
            padding-top: 0;
            padding-left: 1rem;
        }
    }

    .image-wrapper {
        margin-top: 1rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    }

    .service-img {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
        transition: transform 0.3s;
    }

    .image-wrapper:hover .service-img {
        transform: scale(1.02);
    }
</style>
